gw.api.logicalmatch

Class AnonymousBeanKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.domain.AbstractKey
      • gw.api.logicalmatch.AnonymousBeanKey

  • public class AnonymousBeanKey
extends AbstractKey
    Implementation of AbstractKey that can be used to generate a unique key for a bean. This class is constructed via a set of IEntityPropertyInfos, the values of which comprise the key. These keys can be used to quickly determine if key fields of 2 beans are equal.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AnonymousBeanKey

        public AnonymousBeanKey(Bean bean,
                        java.lang.Iterable<? extends IEntityPropertyInfo> identityProperties)
        Creates an AnonymousBeanKey for the given bean and set of identity properties. Can be compared to another AnonymousBeanKey generated for another bean of the same type and fields to see if the given fields are equal.
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean to generate a key for
        identityProperties - the list of properties to compare as part of this key
